<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: US coach banks on high-tech approach
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It may not guarantee success, but the US team has an array of high-tech
gadgets to help them assess rivals teams. Coach Bora Milutinovic's portable
fax machine runs almost non-stop, his tape machines hum and the mail brings
a steady flow of videotapes and publications. Each US player gets an
individualised videotape before each game, analysing opponents' styles and
habits.
The US team played Colombia last night in Los Angeles in their second Group
A game. It is feared that US interest in the tournament will slump if the
home team is brusquely bundled out.
</TEXT>
