<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: S Korean shipyard set for stoppage
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Thousands of workers at the world's largest shipyard, in South Korea, plan
to go on 'temporary strike' during today's Group C match between South Korea
and Bolivia in Boston. The labour union at Hyundai Heavy Industries in
Ulsan, south-east of Seoul, said it plans to call a three-hour stoppage to
enable its 25,000 members to watch the match.
South Korea need to beat the Bolivians if they are to reach the second round
for the first time. They drew 2-2 with Spain last weekend with two goals in
the last six minutes.
