<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Norway braced for Italian backlash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Erland Johnsen and the rest of Norway's defence are bracing themselves for
an Italian backlash in their World Cup Group E clash in New Jersey today.
'E' is considered the toughest of the six first-round groups. Qualifying
matches for the second round continue for another week.
'The Irish did us a favour by showing us that it is possible to play our way
in this heat but they didn't do us a favour by beating Italy,' said the
Chelsea defender. Ireland beat Italy 1-0 last weekend.
The Italians are seeking more than the three points that will put than back
into group contention and restore their battered reputation. 'We have to
play like we're convinced we'll win,' said Italian midfielder Demetrio
Albertini. 'We let Ireland dictate the game to us when it should have been
the other way round.'
Ireland remain favourites to win the group. Johnsen said: 'I'm sure Ireland
will beat Mexico on Friday. They are very similar to us and Mexico will find
it hard to play against that style. They don't like the muscular defensive
play.'
</TEXT>
