<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / Electrolux purchase approved
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HUGH CARNEGY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Electrolux, the world's leading household appliance maker, said yesterday it
had received approval from the European Commission for its DM730m (Pounds
294.3m) acquisition of AEG Hausgerate, the white goods arm of Germany's AEG
industrial group. The takeover, which will now take effect from October 1,
will bring Electrolux alongside Whirlpool of the US in global white goods
sales, extend its lead in total appliance sales and give the Swedish group a
commanding position in Europe's white goods markets. Together, Electrolux
and AEG Hausgerate have annual appliance sales of more than Dollars 9bn.
Combined with AEG, Electrolux will have a white goods market share in
western Europe of at least 25 per cent, against 15-19 per cent for
Bosch-Siemens of Germany and 11-15 per cent for Whirlpool Europe.
The Commission issued its approval of the takeover after a one-month review.
Electrolux said the Commission's main concern had been over its position in
Scandinavian markets, where its share is now set to rise significantly above
its share in other European markets.
