FT  23 JUN 94 / Outsider chosen to lead ICI
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Imperial Chemical Industries, the bulk chemicals company demerged from the
old ICI a year ago, has broken with tradition by appointing outsider Charles
Miller Smith of Unilever as its new chief executive. Miller Smith, a former
Unilever finance director who now runs its food operations in southern
Europe, will take over next April when the present chief executive Ronnie
Hampel will succeed Sir Denys Henderson as chairman.
