<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: Other big moves
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Furniture maker Silentnight was one of the main losers in the London market
after issuing a profits warning at its annual meeting. The shares were off
34 and touched an 18-month low before rallying to finish 24 down at 219p.
Disappointment over its half-year figures saw Quality Care, the nursing home
group, drop 23 to 290p.
Lamont Holdings, the textile group, lost 21 at 403p after it was announced
that investment institution M&amp;G had sold 175,000 shares, reducing its stake
to 3.9m, or 12.98 per cent.
