FT  22 JUN 94 / International Company News: Wine producer acquires brands
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mildura Blass, one of the growing number of quoted wine producers in
Australia, is acquiring the Black Opal and related wine brands from Mr Mark
Cashmore.
The Adelaide-based company has made and marketed the brands since 1990,
under a five-year licensing agreement, and they now account for 13 per cent
of Mildura's total sales volume.
The wines have sold particularly strongly in the US, allowing Mildura to
corner a one-fifth market share of total Australian wine sales there.
Mildura is Australia's fourth largest wine producer.
