second half had improved with a particularly strong performance from the
thermal process division with GCD in Australia being the main contributor.
The thermal process division contributed Pounds 1.93m to operating profits,
against a previous Pounds 881,000, from turnover ahead from Pounds 27.1m to
Pounds 34.1m.
Hydraulics achieved Pounds 1.03m (Pounds 995,000) from turnover of Pounds
13m (Pounds 11.8m).
Earnings per share rose from 8.6p to 12.06p while a recommended final
dividend of 4.5p is proposed for a total distribution of 6.3p (5.6p).
