<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Exceptionals leave Dairy Crest at Pounds 3m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Exceptional items totalling Pounds 35.5m almost wiped out profits at Dairy
Crest, the milk processing and dairy products arm of the Milk Marketing
Board which earlier this month announced the loss of 600 jobs.
The group, which is to be spun off in the changes planned for the milk
market, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.8m, against Pounds 28.2m,
struck after an exceptional charge of Pounds 19m.
Mr John Houliston, chief executive, said that operating profits from
continuing operations, before allowing an Pounds 8m provision for the
recently announced restructuring, had risen 7 per cent, from Pounds 38.6m to
Pounds 41.4m. However, he warned of 'extremely tough' market conditions
which would be reflected in the interim results.
Turnover fell from Pounds 1.16bn to Pounds 997.7m, including Pounds 167.1m
(Pounds 336.4m) from discontinued operations, resulting in sales from
continuing operations being flat at Pounds 830.6m (Pounds 819.4m). On the
same basis operating margins were slightly higher at 5 per cent.
'Dairy Crest continues to make sound progress and is well positioned for the
free market in milk,' he said.
He did not rule out floating part of Dairy Crest before November 1, when the
new milk marketing plans take effect. However, details were not likely for
some weeks.
Exceptional items included losses of Pounds 20.8m on disposals, mainly
reflecting goodwill written back on the sale of five bottling dairies. A 12
per cent in the decline of doorstep milk deliveries led to a provision of
Pounds 9.8m against the book value of the group's diary in Chadwell Heath,
Essex.
The fall in doorstep sales was the main reason for the decline in operating
profits at the food services division from Pounds 23.4m on sales of Pounds
544.2m to Pounds 21.3m on sales of Pounds 505.9m.
Operating profits in consumer foods, which includes liquid milk sales to
supermarkets, rose from Pounds 15.2m to Pounds 20.1m on sales of Pounds
324.7m (Pounds 275.2m).
The disposals helped the group to end the year with net cash of Pounds 23m
compared with net borrowings of Pounds 69.5m previously. Net interest
payable fell from Pounds 8.3m to Pounds 1.5m.
</TEXT>
