FT  22 JUN 94 / Observer: Plumb job
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After last week's Euro-election debacle, it might be thought the remnants of
the Tory MEPs would hunker down and pull together. Instead, they are now
squabbling about who is to be the chairman of their ever-dwindling group.
