FT  22 JUN 94 / Henderson to appear at Scott inquiry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON, Law Courts Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Paul Henderson, the former Matrix Churchill managing director, is to give
oral evidence to the Scott arms-for-Iraq inquiry, it was announced
yesterday.
Mr Henderson, one of three Matrix Churchill directors cleared of the illegal
export of machine tools to Iraq, had asked to give oral evidence after
statements made to the inquiry by Lord Trefgarne, one of three
middle-ranking ministers involved in the alleged relaxation of guidelines
for such exports.
He will give evidence on the points raised by the former minister.
Mr Christopher Muttukumaru, the secretary to the inquiry, said Lord Justice
Scott had also obtained evidence of Mr Henderson's contacts with the
intelligence services.
Mr Henderson would be questioned on some aspects of these contacts, he said.
This part of his evidence would be heard in private at Mr Henderson's
request, he said.
Mr Muttukumaru said Mr Henderson had helped the inquiry from a very early
stage, answering questions and providing written evidence.
Mr Henderson is expected to give his evidence on July 7.
