<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUN 94 / Macedonia border protests
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA SILBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BELGRADE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Macedonia yesterday protested to neighbouring Yugoslavia about several
incursions into Macedonian territory, including the taking of a strategic
hill. The Macedonian Foreign Ministry said yesterday the moves by the
Yugoslav army could have 'unforeseen consequences'. The ministry repeated
calls for an urgent meeting with the government of Yugoslavia, now comprised
of Serbia and Montenegro, to define the border. The protest follows a
warning by the Macedonian chief-of-staff that he would send the army to put
