<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUN 94 / International Company News: Lotus issues warning of sharp
drop in earnings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Lotus Development, the US software company, are expected to come
under pressure today following a profits warning issued late yesterday.
It said earnings per share in the three months to the end of June were
likely to be 20-25 cents, compared with 34 cents a year ago (before a
one-off charge.) Analysts had been expecting earnings of nearly 50 cents a
share for the latest quarter.
Lotus blamed the revision on delays in upgrades to a number of its products.
These upgrades will now be released in July and August, the company said,
leading to what it predicted would be a strong performance in the second
half of the year.
For the year as a whole, Lotus predicted earnings per share of Dollars
1.80-Dollars 2, lower than its previous forecast of Dollars 2-Dollars 2.15.
The company's shares have already fallen sharply in recent months, closing
on Monday at Dollars 51 3/8 , having lost 40 per cent of their value since
the middle of March.
Although first quarter earnings were up by nearly three-quarters on a year
before, sales growth in the first three month of the year was below market
expectations, adding to fears that the company was losing out to Microsoft
in applications software sales.
</TEXT>
